links.answerText: It is George Harrison the Beatle whose first solo album after the band broke up was titled All Things Must Pass.
links.clue: Name the lead guitarist of an iconic British band who released his first solo album after the group broke up in 1970 as a massive triple-LP.
links.hint1: He was the second guitarist of this fabulous band and arguably the most technically sound of the lot.
links.songStartInfo: The song you are listening toMy Sweet Lordis the lead single from that first solo triple-LP album.
triviaItems: George originally gave the song to Billy Preston whose version was more gospel-infused. Georges slide-guitar-heavy arrangement became the definitive global hit.
The third LP, titled Apple Jam, contains a track called "Its Johnnys Birthday" which was a 30th birthday gift for John Lennon.
This record was the catalyst for the formation of Derek and the Dominos as almost the entire backing band (Clapton, Bobby Whitlock, Carl Radle, and Jim Gordon) went on to record Layla.

links.answerText: The Chiffons alleged that George Harrison had subconsciously copied their song Hes So Fine.
links.clue: George Harrison was sued by which famous band for subconsciously plagiarising the melody of My Sweet Lord?
links.hint1: This all woman band was one of the definitive "Girl Groups" of the early 1960s. They became architects of the "Brill Building" sound.
links.songStartInfo: The song you are listening toOne Fine Dayis another hit track from the same album.
triviaItems: The Chiffons opened for The Beatles during their first-ever U.S. tour. George Harrison was likely watching them perform "He's So Fine" from the wings of the stage. years
Lead singer Judy Craig left the group in 1970, for a career in banking, returning to the group in the 1990s.
After the lawsuit ruled against George Harrison, The Chiffons released their own cover of "My Sweet Lord" in 1975, creating a bizarre full-circle moment in pop culture.

links.clue: One Fine Day was co-written by a songwriter who also played piano on this track. She would go on to become a legendary singer-songwriter in her own right. Who is she?
links.hint1: She was part of a legendary "songwriting factory" in Manhattan where she worked with her then-husband Gerry Goffin.
links.songStartInfo: Carole Kings 1971 solo album Tapestry became one of the best-selling records of all time. This song was one of her best known hits.

links.answerText: It was Paul Simon (performing under the stage name Jerry Landis) who paired up with Carole King (then Carol Klein). The song you are listening to is one of the most iconic of his solo career.
links.clue: In 1958, while she was a student at Queens College in New York, Carole King recorded demos with another musician who went on to be famous in his own right. Name that singer.
links.hint1: He was part of a legendary duo probably best known for their Concert in Central Park
links.songTitle: Diamonds On the Soles of Her Shoes

links.answerText: Ray Phiri happened to be in New York with Paul Simon to appear on Saturday Night Live. when he was invited by Steve to contribute his unique, snaking guitar lines to Higher Love.
links.clue: The lead guitarist on Diamonds on the Soles of her Feet, was a South African musician who also played the iconic riff on this massive hit by Steve Winwood. Name the song.
links.hint1: This song's lyrics describe a 'blind' search for a spiritual force that moves and 'shines.
multipleChoiceOptions: Back in the High Life Again
